reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nicely made, Good price
reviews.reviewText: Honestly I can't hear a difference in sound with this cable over the stock cable that came with my IEMs. BUT I prefer braided cables because they're less stiff and don't transmit sounds when they brush against my clothes. This cable has a nice feel, appears to be made with quality components. It's very good value for the money, definitely comparable to a much more expensive Fiio cable I ordered last year.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great versatile cable
reviews.reviewText: This is a very nice soft cable that has a nice tight weave to it. It sounds great, and the connectors are high-quality. There are no ear hooks so it work with straight down connectors or can be worn over the ear. The chin-slider has to be my favorite for any cable I own, and all the connectors are a nice appropriately weighty metal, without being too heavy to overly weigh the cable down or anything like that. I highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars High distortion and unpredictability
reviews.reviewText: I've had this cable for a few months and can confidently recommend you avoid it. The build quality isn't great, but the microphone play pause circuit is very poorly sealed. Any slight movement even while seated will trigger a pause, rendering this cable useless. The audio quality is passable for recording, however it's useless for calls due to the aforementioned distortion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good flexible cable but the mic is trash
reviews.reviewText: Bought the cable to have a microphone. The thing doesn't even work right. Tested with zoom and it's lower than the microphone array on my laptop. The cable itself is alright. Flexible and looks pretty. You should buy this only if your oem cable is stiff and has microphonics. Don't buy for the microphone

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good replacement for worn out in-ear cord.
reviews.reviewText: We use in-ear monitors extensively in our band and, over time, the cords stiffen and are less comfortable to wear. These serve as very good replacements. If I had any criticism, it would be that I'd prefer metal connectors over plastic, but for the price these are fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seems well made so far. Decent mic
reviews.reviewText: I bought this because the stock cable on my Fiio/Jadeaudio EA1s didn't stay put, and doesn't have a mic. This one has a mic, and it stays in place. I'm happy. Sound quality is exactly the same as before, as expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It's a decent cable
reviews.reviewText: I got the USB-C QDC cable and to start it's a nicely constructed cable. It's thick and seemingly durable, however there's quite a bit of memory from the packaging. There's also no formed ear hooks so you have to wrap it around everytime you want to use your headphones and sometimes they just come undone from behind the ear. Lastly the dac is low quality for the price, you can find the same chip in $9 usb-c dongles. Overall it's convenient to not have the dongle and if you have a cheap KZ IEM then this will definitely be an upgrade to whatever cable came with your IEMs

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Attractive cable for my Fiio FH3
reviews.reviewText: Made well. Looks great. Supple and easy to store. I use it with my Fiio FH3 IEMs. Works flawlessly. My only note is that the chin adjuster is a little difficult to move around, but it wasn’t a dealbreaker for me. Delivers quality sound if listening to hifi/hi-res audio.
Me gusta el diseño del cable, parece ser muy resistente y me gusta la construcción del cable.Se nota que es un cable de alta calidad.

Solid cable, the best of the three I've had (including and especially the actual Shure ones). The cable just gets a bit more stiff around the ears, which is a great compromise between the hard plastic and totally limp options. I've only had it a couple weeks so I also can't comment on durability. It works well, sounds good. I used it with upper end Shures.Edit: Still working well after 9 months or so of regular use.
Had to replace the cables of my Moondrop Blessing 2 Dusk, was a little worried about buying this third party cable, but the build, durability, and sound quality is all perfect 👍
Love this cable. It's not too long, sturdy, affordable, and isn't thin and flimsy. Also has a subtle, retro copper look that's muted in person.
